ODE XXIV

Addressed to Virgil by Horace on the unexpected death of their common friend Quintilius Varus. of Quintilius (probably Quintilius Varus, cf. 1. 18. 1 ; A.P. 438) our chief knowledge is that he died in B.c. 24, and was a native of Cremona, but his name is enshrined in this Ode for immortality.
